<TITLE> Azizul off to US to attend WB-IMF meeting </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 17 (bdnews24.com) - Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam left Dhaka for Washington Wednesday to attend the annual meeting of the World Bank and International Monetary Fund scheduled for Oct 20-22. The adviser will lead a five-member delegation that includes Bangladesh Bank governor Salehuddin Ahmed, finance secretary Mohammad Tareq and Economic Relations Division secretary Aminul Islam Bhuiyan. Zakir Ahmed Khan, WB Board alternate director, will join the Bangladesh side from his station in Washington, the finance ministry's spokesperson Fazle Rabbi told bdnews24.com. Azizul will fly to New York from Washington on Oct 23 to attend a global dialogue on financing for development, Rabbi said. The adviser will return on Nov 1. At the annual meeting, member country officials are given a platform to share their development experiences. The two multilateral lending agencies aim to attain an inclusive and sustainable global growth rate wherein the world's poorest can enjoy more of the benefits of growth. Participants at the event are generally key private sector players, government delegates and senior bank and fund officials. The WB and IMF boards of governors meet once a year at the annual meeting to discuss ongoing work and new initiatives undertaken by their respective institutions. The annual meeting generally takes place in September or October. bdnew
